qas.question: What was the Victorian era of the United Kingdom?

answers.text: the period of Queen Victoria's reign

qas.question: Through what Period did Queen Victoria reign?
What did the people consider Queen Victoria reign to be?

answers.text: a long period of prosperity for the British people

qas.question: How far back would some scholars extend Victoria's reign?

answers.text: five years to the passage of the Reform Act 1832.

context: The Victorian era of the United Kingdom was <a0_0>the period of Queen Victoria's reign<a0_0/> from June <a1_0>1837 to January 1901<a1_0/>. This was <a2_0>a long period of prosperity for the British people<a2_0/>, as profits gained from the overseas British Empire, as well as from industrial improvements at home, allowed a large, educated middle class to develop. Some scholars would extend the beginning of the period—as defined by a variety of sensibilities and political games that have come to be associated with the Victorians—back <a3_0>five years to the passage of the Reform Act 1832.
